BEWARE!!! To celebrate the Lunar New Year with my husband and 2 kids, I decided to place an order on their website directly instead of seamless so they didn’t have to pay third party fees. HUGE MISTAKE. Placed the order online at 7:33pm, was given an estimated time of 50 mins for delivery, which I thought was reasonable because of the holiday. However, after still waiting for our order at 8:45pm, I emailed AND started calling the restaurant to see where my order was. The line was busy but I finally got through at 9pm. The lady who picked up asked, “Are you calling to see where your order is?” When I answered yes, she then proceeded to say, “All the seamless orders have been sent out, but the other orders were cancelled.” WHAT?! I understand if they got overwhelmed with holiday orders, but it was an intentional decision on their end to prioritize only the seamless orders and then to essentially ignore/disregard the others. NO PHONE CALL, NO EMAIL, NOTHING to communicate that they couldn’t handle the order 1.5 HOURS AFTER I placed my order. Needless to say, they totally ruined our evening. NEVER EVER ordering from them again and telling everyone we know to STAY AWAY. I don’t care how good their food is, this is totally unprofessional, irresponsible and not the way to run a business.

Mr Wonton exceeded my expectations on my first delivery order. I wanted to get something healthy so ordered various greens - chinese broccoli, mustard greens, bok choy w mushrooms - and requested “no starch-sugar-msg” in the special requests box and... they actually followed the request!! The dishes were all delicious. They were also delivered ridiculously fast and the guy who dropped them off was polite!! I am also so happy to see that they have “many” options for chinese greens - not just one. I will go there to try them for dim sum, but when I order, I really like to order various kinds of chinese greens and most places don’t do this and/or they pile on starchy or sweet sauces. Six stars for Mr Wonton! (The prawns were excellent, too.)

Today was my first time here, and I am glad that I stopped by. Some of the reviews stated that their wontons were good, and I agree! This was recommended by a previous reviewer, and for that, I am very thankful.  Lastly, I ordered their Steamed Shrimp Shumai. This caught me by surprise as I love the small, bite size ones you find in Japanese places. They are bigger here and seasoned differently. They were good, but I do not expect to get them again. Perhaps the chicken version will meet my preferences.  The service was good and the staff was very friendly with everyone that walked in. The bathroom was also clean and well stocked with soap and paper towels.  I will gladly come back and sample more dishes.

This was my first time being in contact with this restaurant. I called and said "Hi there, how much would it be for shrimp with mixed vegetables and fried rice?" He tells me "nine fifty" ($9.50) I say, "okay, and if I was to swap the shrimp for chicken instead, how much would it be then?" He replies "same price, nine fifty" so I said "okay thank you very much." I give my friend money to grab it for us. He gets there and they tell him "nine fifty where?! Go somewhere else!" He calls me and tells me this.  I asked him "what? Let me speak to them" my friend goes "no, I'm not letting her touch my phone after being nasty with me. We going to order somewhere else." I call a few mins after and I ask "why did you tell me it was $9.50 for the shrimp mixed vegetables and fried rice and tell my friend that it's not and to go somewhere else?" She argues with me. She talks over me without letting me speak and I say "okay, I'll write a review for you. Bye"  I'm clueless on why she was being a disgusting human being? But the other guy was nice over the phone. Whatever, everything happens for my own benefit. I probably would've ate something awful and wasted my money. So thank you, beautiful universe! :)

I have been getting delivery from Mr.Wonton for about two years now and I noticed something. If you do not pay attention the delivery person will snatch your money and run.  Especially if the weather is bad outside and he knows that you have no shoes on.  He snatched five extra dollars from my son and now he just snatched 20 extra dollars from my daughter with me standing right behind her.  When we called the shop the first time they claimed that they will credit my account.  This time they said that he deserved a 23 dollar tip for a 39 dollar food delivery.  Although the food is better than the restaurants around my house it is not the best Chinese take out I've tasted.  That 20 dollar snatch just lost them a customer.
